SIMPLE: truth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Truth
<hw>Truth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Truths</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>treuthe</ets>,
<ets>trouthe</ets>, <ets>treowpe</ets>, AS. <ets>tre⟦oacute⟧w<?/</ets>.
See <er>True</er>; cf. <er>Troth</er>, <er>Betroth</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or being true; as: -- <sd>(a)</sd>
Conformity to fact or reality; exact accordance with that which is, or
has been; or shall be.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Conformity to rule; exactness; close correspondence
with an example, mood, object of imitation, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Plows, to go true, depend much on the <qex>truth</qex> of the
ironwork.</q> <rj><qau>Mortimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <def>Fidelity; constancy; steadfastness;
faithfulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Alas! they had been friends in youth,⟦br⟧
But whispering tongues can poison <qex>truth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(d)</sd> <def>The practice of speaking what is true; freedom from
falsehood; veracity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If this will not suffice, it must appear⟦br⟧
That malice bears down <qex>truth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is true or certain concerning any matter
or subject, or generally on all subjects; real state of things; fact;
verity; reality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Speak ye every man the <xex>truth</xex> to his neighbor.</q>
<rj><qau>Zech. viii. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I long to know the <qex>truth</qex> here of at large.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>truth</qex> depends on, or is only arrived at by, a
legitimate deduction from all the facts which are truly material.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A true thing; a verified fact; a true statement or
proposition; an established principle, fixed law, or the like; <as>as,
the great <ex>truths</ex> of morals</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Even so our boasting . . . is found a <qex>truth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Cor. vii. 14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Righteousness; true religion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Grace and <qex>truth</qex> came by Jesus Christ.</q> <rj><qau>John
i. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sanctify them through thy <qex>truth</qex>; thy word is
<qex>truth</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>John xvii. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>In truth</b></col>, <cd>in reality; in fact.</cd> --
<col><b>Of a truth</b></col>, <cd>in reality; certainly.</cd> --
<col><b>To do truth</b></col>, <cd>to practice what God
commands.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that <qex>doeth truth</qex> cometh to the light.</q>
<rj><qau>John iii. 21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Truth
<hw>Truth</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To assert as true; to
declare.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Had they [the ancients] dreamt this, they would have
<qex>truthed</qex> it heaven.</q> <rj><qau>Ford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truthful</ent>⟦br⟧
